<br>
As for the Faer, they're just the other side of the same coin.  At the extreme, you have the do-gooder medling in everyone else's business on the assumption that she knows what's good and right for everyone (this is pretty much the same thing as the hate-mongering Tier that meddles for his own ends).  At the lesser extreme, there are the simple Faer that exist only to pursue knowledge.<br>
<br>
Basically, both races use their heritage to justify actions that they wish to indulge in and would perform regardless of race or religion.  They're all the same.  As the saying goes, &quot;Elves is elves&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1>Firiona Vie General Chat</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href="http://www.firionavie.org/">Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.firiona-vie.com/fvchat.html" target="_blank"><h3>Chat Room</a></h3></center> <br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  